                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1133">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJC1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1916-11-02T18:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 2, 1916, 6 p. m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3539. Your 4535, October 27, 12 p. m. In view of seriousness of the consequences
                    which may result from proposed policy in Belgium, aside from humanitarian
                    considerations, you are authorized to request an interview with the Chancellor.
                    Department leaves it to your discretion as to extent your informal
                    representations with Chancellor should go, which must necessarily be guided by
                    circumstances and upon his general attitude in matter. It should be pointed out
                    to him, however, unfortunate impression proposed policy would create in neutral
                    countries, and especially in United States, which has welfare of Belgian civil
                    population very much at heart.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
